LESSON 7 SENTENCE PATTERNS

these are the fundamental structures of english
bond patterns teach valid word orders

pattern: I plus verb

PATHWAY i_am | from: i | to: am | strength: 0.9
PATHWAY i_have | from: i | to: have | strength: 0.8
PATHWAY i_feel | from: i | to: feel | strength: 0.8
PATHWAY i_think | from: i | to: think | strength: 0.8
PATHWAY i_know | from: i | to: know | strength: 0.8
PATHWAY i_want | from: i | to: want | strength: 0.7
PATHWAY i_see | from: i | to: see | strength: 0.7
PATHWAY i_like | from: i | to: like | strength: 0.7
PATHWAY i_love | from: i | to: love | strength: 0.7
PATHWAY i_remember | from: i | to: remember | strength: 0.7
PATHWAY i_understand | from: i | to: understand | strength: 0.7

pattern: it plus is or was

PATHWAY it_is | from: it | to: is | strength: 0.9
PATHWAY it_was | from: it | to: was | strength: 0.8

pattern: you plus are or were

PATHWAY you_are | from: you | to: are | strength: 0.9

pattern: that plus is

PATHWAY that_is | from: that | to: is | strength: 0.8

pattern: there plus is

PATHWAY there_is | from: there | to: is | strength: 0.8

pattern: article plus noun

PATHWAY the_thing | from: the | to: thing | strength: 0.5
PATHWAY the_world | from: the | to: world | strength: 0.5
PATHWAY the_way | from: the | to: way | strength: 0.5
PATHWAY the_truth | from: the | to: truth | strength: 0.5
PATHWAY the_light | from: the | to: light | strength: 0.5

pattern: adjective plus noun

PATHWAY good_thing | from: good | to: thing | strength: 0.4
PATHWAY little_thing | from: little | to: thing | strength: 0.4
PATHWAY beautiful_world | from: beautiful | to: world | strength: 0.4

pattern: adverb plus adjective

PATHWAY very_good | from: very | to: good | strength: 0.5
PATHWAY really_good | from: really | to: good | strength: 0.5
PATHWAY very_happy | from: very | to: happy | strength: 0.5

